Description: Oblong, thick and flat artefact made of Nile silt clay, with two deep and almost semi-cylindrical holes in the middle of one side, possibly a kind of lid with grip holes or a figure-stand with mortises for the feet of a statuette.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.57, p.178, pl.20)
